SIMPLE: bioscope
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bioscope
<hw>Bi"o*scope</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>bi`os</grk> life + <ets>-scope</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
view of life; that which gives such a view.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Bagman's <qex>Bioscope</qex>: Various Views of Men and Manners.
<mark>[<it>Book Title</it>.]</mark></q> <rj><qau>W. Bayley
(1824).</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An animated picture machine for screen projection; a
cinematograph (which see); an archaic term replaced by <er>movie
projector</er>.</def> <mark>[archaic]</mark> ⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>a South African movie theater.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Biostatics</ent>⟦br⟧
